<h4>ARTICLES &amp; TALKS</h4>
<p><a href="http://howistart.org/posts/go/1">How I Start: Go</a><br />A well-written guide to creating a simple HTTP service from scratch</p>
<p><a href="http://talks.golang.org/2014/hammers.slide#1">Gophers with Hammers</a><br />How Go's design facilitates writing tools for Go</p>
<p><a href="https://blog.splice.com/iota-elegant-constants-golang/">iota: elegant constants in Go</a><br />A detailed look at using constants expressively, with particular attention to `iota`</p>
<p><a href="http://blog.golang.org/constants">Constants: The Go Blog</a><br />"In Go, constants, unlike variables, behave pretty much like regular numbers. This post explains why that is and what it means."</p>
<p><a href="https://blog.splice.com/lesser-known-features-go-test/">Lesser-known features of `go test`</a><br />Including parallel tests and blackbox testing</p>
<p><a href="http://blog.cloudflare.com/go-interfaces-make-test-stubbing-easy">Go interfaces make test stubbing easy</a></p>
<p><a href="https://docs.google.com/document/d/1nr-TQHw_er6GOQRsF6T43GGhFDelrAP0NqSS_00RgZQ/preview?sle=true">Go execution modes</a><br />Proposals for different execution modes for shared library support and possible linking to non-Go programs</p>
<p><a href="http://www.gophercon.in/blog/2014/08/19/blakeinterview/">Interview: GopherConIndia Speaker Blake Mizerany</a><br />A short interview with Blake Mizerany (check the blog for other interesting interviews).</p>
<p><a href="http://blog.matttproud.com/2014/09/go-testing-patterns-benchmark-setup-and.html">Go testing patterns: benchmarking and expensive fixture setup, allocations, and automation</a><br />Following on from Dave Cheney's post on using pkg/testing for microbenchmarks</p>
<p><a href="http://dave.cheney.net/2014/09/01/gos-runtime-c-to-go-rewrite-by-the-numbers">Go&rsquo;s runtime C to Go rewrite, by the numbers</a></p>
<p><a href="http://www.goinggo.net/2014/09/go-compiler-nil-pointer-checks.html">Go compiler nil pointer checks</a><br />A low-level look at nil pointer checks</p>
<p><a href="https://speakerdeck.com/joho/ruby-rails-and-go">Ruby, Rails &amp; Go</a><br />"Comparing and contrasting Ruby on Rails and Go from the human perspective."</p>
<h4>NEW &amp; UPDATED PACKAGES</h4>
<p><a href="https://github.com/blevesearch/bleve">blevesearch/bleve</a><br />A modern text indexing library for Go</p>
<p><a href="https://github.com/Yelp/dockersh">Yelp/dockersh</a><br />A shell which places users into individual docker containers</p>
<p><a href="https://github.com/tv42/jsonarray">tv42/jsonarray</a><br />Streaming decoder for JSON arrays</p>
<p><a href="http://agocs.org/blog/2014/08/19/rabbitmq-best-practices-in-go/">Using Go to load test a RabbitMQ instance</a></p>
<p><a href="https://github.com/tomjowitt/ozdata">tomjowitt/ozdata</a><br />Australian postcode data query tool</p>
<p><a href="https://github.com/ConradIrwin/aws-name-server">ConradIrwin/aws-name-server</a></p>
